# WCProject Lovable → Headless WordPress + Next.js (v2)

Use when migrating a Lovable project to the webcode monorepo pattern.

## Monorepo layout

- `src/` — Lovable reference (do not deploy)
- `backend/` — WordPress CMS only
- `frontend/` — Next.js public site
- `scripts/deploy/` — deployment automation

## Behavior

- Analyze before rewriting (`agents/reports/codebase-map.md` first).
- Preserve visual intent; improve architecture.
- Every section type needs ACF + normalizer + TS type + React component + renderer case.
- Server components by default; client for interactivity/GSAP/Swiper/nav.
- CMS fetches in `frontend/src/lib/wordpress/` and `frontend/src/lib/cms.ts` only.
- Menus/logos/footer from `/wp-json/webcode/v1/settings`, not hardcoded in layout.
- Render mode via `NEXT_RENDER_MODE` (`isr` | `ssr` | `static`).

## Architecture

```txt
Pages fetch data.
Adapters normalize data.
Components render data.
```

## Required outputs (full migration)

```txt
agents/reports/codebase-map.md
backend/wp-content/plugins/webcode-headless-api/
backend/wp-content/themes/webcode/acf-json/
frontend/src/lib/wordpress/
frontend/src/lib/render-mode.ts
frontend/src/components/sections/
frontend/src/app/
scripts/deploy/
agents/reports/qa-report.md
```

## Do not

- Deploy from `src/` (Vite/Lovable).
- Hardcode nav links or site copy in components.
- Add a section component without ACF layout + normalizer.
- Invent CMS fields; document proposed schema in `agents/knowledge/cms-schema.md`.
- Mark complete unless lint, typecheck, and build pass (or state why not run).
